 Evidence-Appreciation of oral evidence Of different witnesses , explained-where the oral evidence supported by circumstantial evidence lead only to one possible view of guilt and no two views were reasonably possible , the accused must be held guilty of the offence charged-Trap witnesses , evidentiary value of-Sentence-When the statute prescribes a minimum sentence , the fact that offence was committed long back or that the accused retired from service will be of no avail.
 
